{"key":"processedPost-8820667","value":{"id":8820667,"first":8820224,"last":8820667,"when":1219613362,"utime":"08/25/08 12:29 AM","content":"Give it a rest.<br /><br />It's common, especially in commercial mushroom farms to place a thick layer of salt over a small spot of trichoderma that shows up during a flush.&nbsp; Doing so can sometimes buy you an extra few days.&nbsp; I've used it on casing layers and straw logs.&nbsp; Each time, the layer of salt killed off the spot of mold. Extend the salt layer about 1\" beyond any green you see. It's not for when&nbsp; your whole tray is contaminated, but if there's a small spot and your fruits are approaching harvest, it will&nbsp; buy you the time they need to finish.<br />RR","title":"Re: Bleach vs. Salt"}}